race.comment: LEONI BALE (1) has mixed form recently, finishing fifth (29.72) in a Grade 5 at Wentworth Park latest but did run well two back when in the frame. Meets a moderate line up and rates on top this time. INDENTATIONS (8) turned in a solid run last start over 330m at this track finishing 4th and beaten only 2.25 lengths (19.14). Has a good record here at this journey. Should be in this for a long way. LONE SHARK (6) goes very well here starting 26 times for nine wins and 10 minors. Comes off a (26.04) win last time, scoring by half a length in a Grade 4/5 over 457m at this track. Looks a key chance on best figures. LAGNICOURT (2) is in form and must include among the chances.
